      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4><span lang=\"EN\">Solving a System of Equations by Elimination</span></h4>\n<p></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN\">Let&rsquo;s\n    reinforce the steps to solve a system of equations using elimination.</span></p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"618\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 1:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"> Write both equations in standard form. If any\n            coefficients are fractions, clear them.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 2:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"> Check to see if the coefficients of one variable are\n            opposites. If so, proceed to Step 3. If not, we will cover that in the next\n            lesson.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 3:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"> Add the equations resulting from Step 2 to eliminate\n            one variable.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 4</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"><strong>:</strong> Solve for the remaining variable.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 5:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"> Substitute the solution from Step 4 into one of the\n            original equations. Then solve for the other variable.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 6</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"><strong>: </strong>Write the solution as an ordered pair.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"618\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step 7:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\"> Check that the ordered pair is a solution to both\n            original equations.<strong></strong></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Example</span></strong></p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN\">Let&rsquo;s look\n    at an example. Solve the following system of equations using elimination:</span></p>\n<p>\\(\\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}3x-3y=-24\\\\\\;-3x+5y=30\\end{array}\\right.\\)</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"618\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              1: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Write\n            both equations in standard form. If any coefficients are fractions, clear\n            them.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(3x - 3y = -24\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(-3x + 5y = 30\\)</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              2: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Check\n            to see if the coefficients of one variable are opposites or equivalent.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">The coefficients on the \\(x\\)-variables are\n            opposites. We can add the equations.</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              3: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Add\n            the equations to eliminate one variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n            &nbsp;\\(3x - 3y = -24\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <u>&nbsp;\\(-3x + 5y = 30\\)</u></span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(2y = 6\\) </span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              4: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Solve\n            for the remaining variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n            \\(2y = 6\\)&nbsp;</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n            <i></i>\\(y = 3\\)&nbsp;</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              5: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Substitute\n            the solution from Step 4 into one of the original equations. Then solve for\n            the other variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(3x - 3y = -24\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN\">\\(3x - 3(3) = -24\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(3x - 9 = -24\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(3x &nbsp;= -15\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(x &nbsp;= -5\\)</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              6: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Write\n            the solution as an ordered pair.</span></p>\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; \\((-5,\n            3)\\)</span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n              7: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Check\n            that the ordered pair is a solution to both original equations.</span><strong><span lang=\"EN\"></span></strong></p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(3x - 3y = -24\\) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(-3x + 5y = 30\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;\\(3(-5) - 3(3) = -24\\)</span><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; \\(-3(-5) + 5(3) = 30\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(-15 - 9 = -24\\) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(15 + 15 = 30\\)</span></p>\n        <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(-24 = -24\\) &nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\">\u2714</span><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;\\(30 = 30\\)&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\">\u2714</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h4><span lang=\"EN\">Try\n    It: Solving a System of Equations by Elimination</span></h4>\n<p><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventnameX\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <p><span lang=\"EN\">Solve the following system of equations using elimination:</span></p>\n    <p><span lang=\"EN\">\\(\\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}4x-6y=8\\\\x+6y=17\\end{array}\\right.\\)</span></p>\n    <p></p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p></p>\n    <p><span lang=\"EN\">Write\n        down your answer. Then select the <strong>Solution\n        </strong>button to check your work.</span></p>\n    <p></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"eventnameX\">\n  <p></p>\n  <p><span lang=\"EN\">Here is\n      how to solve this system of equations using elimination:</span></p>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"618\">\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                1: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Write\n              both equations in standard form. If any coefficients are fractions, clear\n              them.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              \\( 4x - 6y = 8 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              \\( x + 6y = 17 \\)</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                2: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Check\n              to see if the coefficients of one variable are opposites.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">The coefficients on the \\(y\\)-variables are opposites.</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                3: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Add\n              the equations resulting from Step 2 to eliminate one variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              \\( 4x - 6y = 8 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>\\(x + 6y = 17 \\)</u><u></u></span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              \\( 5x = 25\\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                4: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Solve\n              for the remaining variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\( 5x = 25 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              <i></i>\\( x = 5 \\)</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                5: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Substitute\n              the solution from Step 4 into one of the original equations. Then solve for\n              the other variable.</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \\( 4x - 6y = 8 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>\\( 4(5) - 6y = 8 \\)<span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;\\( 20 - 6y = 8 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\( -6y = -12 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\\( y = 2 \\)</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                6: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Write\n              the solution as an ordered pair.</span></p>\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; \\((5,\n              2)\\)</span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><strong><span lang=\"EN\">Step\n                7: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\">Check\n              that the ordered pair is a solution to both original equations.</span><strong><span lang=\"EN\"></span></strong></p>\n        </td>\n        <td valign=\"top\" width=\"309\">\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n              \\( 4x - 6y = 8 \\)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \\( x + 6y = 17 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; \\(4(5) - 6(2) = 8\\) &nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\( 5 + 6(2) = 17 \\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(20 - 12 = 8\\) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(5 +\n              12 = 17\\)</span></p>\n          <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(8 = 8\\) &nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\">\u2714</span><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \\(17 = 17\\)&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\">\u2714</span><span lang=\"EN\"></span></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n  <p><span lang=\"EN\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\"><br></span></p>\n  <p><span lang=\"EN\">How did you do? </span><span lang=\"EN\">Know that you learn more from wrong answers than from right answers!\n      Wrong answers help us find flaws in our thinking. Take a minute to think\n      about <i>why </i>you got the question\n      wrong. Then you won&rsquo;t get this type of question wrong again!</span></p>\n</div>"
    }
  ]
}